description: From Middle English *overfillen, oferfüllen, from Old English oferfyllan (“to cram, overfill”), equivalent to over- +‎ fill. Cognate with Middle Low German overfullen, German überfüllen, Danish overfylde, Swedish överfylla.

verbs.description: overfill (third-person singular simple present overfills, present participle overfilling, simple past and past participle overfilled)

entries.meaning: To fill beyond capacity or beyond what is appropriate.
